// =============================================================================
// core.architecture — ATS-V Architectural Type System library
// =============================================================================
//
// **Verum-native canonical types for the Architectural Type System.**
//
// Under the reuse-over-invention discipline, the ATS-V extension
// is implemented as:
//
//   1. ONE typed attribute — `@arch_module(...)` — recognised by the
//      compiler-internal dispatch (V8.1 META1 architectural principle,
//      grammar/verum.ebnf generic `identifier(args)` form).
//
//   2. THIS library — Verum-native `type X is variant_list`
//      declarations that mirror the kernel-side `verum_kernel::arch*`
//      primitives.  Both sides stay aligned via the cross-side pin
//      test in `crates/verum_kernel/tests/k_arch_v_alignment.rs`,
//      which fails CI on any drift.
//
//   3. Per-module kernel-discharge bridges declared as
//      `@kernel_discharge(<intrinsic>)` axioms — one per architectural
//      sub-system.
//
// **Architectural alignment** mirrors `core.verify.separation_soundness`
// (#161) and `core.verify.codegen_soundness` (#162): kernel-discharge
// pattern with `@kernel_discharge(<intrinsic>)` annotations.
//
// **Module roster** (10 modules, full ATS-V surface coverage):
//
//   1. `types.vr` — canonical primitives (Capability / Boundary /
//      Composition / Lifecycle / Foundation / Tier / MsfsStratum /
//      CveClosure / Shape / CapabilitySchema) + pure-data helpers.
//   2. `capability_ontology.vr` — registered Custom capability names.
//   3. `anti_patterns.vr` — full 32-pattern roster (AntiPatternCode /
//      AntiPatternViolation / Severity / DiagnosticContext) + 12
//      kernel-discharge bridges.
//   4. `mtac.vr` — Modal-Temporal Architectural Calculus primitives
//      + helpers (time_point_precedes, observer_full_canonical_roster,
//      modal_is_temporal/is_modal, adjunction_witness_is_adjoint_of).
//   5. `counterfactual.vr` — non-destructive counterfactual reasoning
//      engine (ArchMetric / MetricValue / InvariantStatus /
//      CounterfactualReport).
//   6. `adjunction.vr` — adjunction analyzer for refactoring
//      (CanonicalAdjunction / Refactoring / AdjunctionAnalysis /
//      RefactoringChain).
//   7. `yoneda.vr` — Yoneda-equivalence checker (ShapeObservation /
//      AgreementStatus / YonedaVerdict).
//   8. `composition.vr` — A ⊗ B typed operation (CompositionResult)
//      with associativity pin.
//   9. `corpus.vr` — cross-cog invariants (CorpusInvariant /
//      CorpusViolation / CorpusReport, 4 baseline checks).
//  10. `phase.vr` — ATS-V phase 6.5 orchestrator surface
//      (ModuleArchResult / ArchPhaseReport / CompositionStep /
//      CompositionVerificationReport).
//  11. `parse.vr` — `@arch_module(...)` parser error type
//      (ArchParseError, 5 variants) + canonical-field roster pin.
// =============================================================================

@arch_module(
    foundation: Foundation.ZfcTwoInacc,
    stratum: MsfsStratum.LFnd,
    lifecycle: Lifecycle.Theorem("v0.1"),
)
module core.architecture.mod;

